headline: Uber Stock Got Crushed by Tesla Fears. The Case for Buying Now.

headline: Uber launches new rides to capitalize on Thanksgiving travel demand
summary: The Uber XXL service, catered toward airport travel, is available in more than 60 airports globally, including 40 in the United States and Canada, the company said.  Uber has been looking to reinvigorate demand, as it grapples with a weakening ride-hailing market due to economic uncertainty and high inflation impacting commuters.  CEO Dara Khosrowshahi said last month that the company plans to capture suburban markets in the U.S. by focusing on features that allow users to reserve and wait for rides.
